Karl, 
You layed some hydralic lifter's on a solid cam? Are the push rods a
different length? 
I never could figure out why in the heck hydralics couldn't be put in an
engine with a solid lifter cam. 
Both cams are hardened. 
The face of the lifter regardless of what type it is is hardened, so it
shouldn't wear out. 
What is the big deal?
Sounds llike a reasonable set-up to me. 
